\begin{rSection}{Projects}

%-------------------------------------------
% HCC circRNA
%-------------------------------------------
\textbf{HCC Prediction with circRNA using Ensemble Heterogeneous Graph Attention Networks} \hfill \textit{Mar. 2024 -- Dec. 2024} \\
\hspace*{0.5em} \textit{Keywords: Bioinformatics, circRNA, Hepatocellular carcinoma, Heterogeneous, Graph, Ensemble}
[\href{https://drive.google.com/file/d/14Jb0DGuJ3rtw9oVpDX8h-zFtCXwUOFBz/view?usp=drive_link}{Paper} $|$ 
\href{https://github.com/janghana/HCC-Prediction-with-circRNA-using-Ensemble-Heterogeneous-Graph-Attention-Networks}{Code} $|$ 
\href{https://drive.google.com/file/d/1wL0qKHLMqsJQ5L3oL_iSEl03YpwCQRZw/view}{Awards} $|$ 
\href{https://drive.google.com/file/d/1mUGoFzGKtcTUVR2UUFi4breL0e4KBnFk/view}{Poster}] \\
\hspace*{1em} Circular RNA (circRNA) is a type of non-coding RNA showing high stability and abundance, making it a potential biomarker in cancer research. This project focuses on predicting HCC using circRNA data by integrating heterogeneous graph attention networks and XGBoost. The approach leverages the resilience of circRNA in body fluids as a non-invasive biomarker, potentially improving early detection and precision treatment strategies for liver cancer. \\
\hspace*{1em} Constructed a heterogeneous attention network to capture complex circRNA–gene interactions.  
\hspace*{1em} Incorporated an ensemble approach combining graph embeddings with XGBoost to refine predictive performance.

%-------------------------------------------
% Unsupervised Diffusion T1
%-------------------------------------------
\bigskip
\textbf{Unsupervised Diffusion Model for Synthesizing T1-weighted MRI Scans from Abdominal CT Scans} \hfill \textit{Dec. 2023 -- Jun. 2024} \\
\textit{Keywords: Computer Vision, Medical Imaging, Generative Models, Diffusion Models, Medical Registration} \quad
[\href{https://www.dbpia.co.kr/journal/articleDetail?nodeId=NODE11862432}{Paper} $|$ 
\href{https://github.com/janghana/Unsupervised-Diffusion-Model-for-Synthesizing-T1-weighted-MRI-Scans-from-Abdominal-CT-Scans}{Code} $|$ 
\href{https://drive.google.com/file/d/1J3rnoVAd6anQrsf-7kLHkHUhdYOFSOmN/view?usp=drive_link}{Poster}] \\
\hspace*{1em} Proposed a cyclic diffusive generative model for translating CT to T1-weighted MRI, aiming to reduce high costs and long acquisition times of MRI scans. This approach leverages adversarial diffusion techniques, preserving tissue detail from CT while synthesizing MRI-like contrast. \\
\hspace*{1em} Implemented a cycle-consistent diffusion framework to stabilize CT-to-MRI translation.  
\hspace*{1em} Demonstrated potential cost-saving benefits in clinical environments by reducing additional MRI scans.

%-------------------------------------------
% Breast Cancer ViT
%-------------------------------------------
\bigskip
\textbf{Enhancing Breast Cancer MRI Classification Through ViT and Multi-Marker Integration} \hfill \textit{Sep. 2023 -- Dec. 2023} \\
\textit{Keywords: Computer Vision, Medical Imaging, 3D Medical Image Classification, Breast Cancer, ER, PR, HER2} \quad
[\href{https://drive.google.com/file/d/14jp4KGZlAj2tE1xGyHQD4Unks2Ln5WNx/view}{Paper} $|$ 
\href{https://github.com/janghana/Breast-Cancer-Classification-using-ViT}{Code}] \\
\hspace*{1em} Focused on augmenting breast cancer classification in MRI by incorporating multiple biomarkers (ER, PR, HER2) alongside cancer labels. Demonstrated that multi-marker synergy could outperform single-marker models, revealing non-invasive ways to probe protein expressions in breast cancer. \\
\hspace*{1em} Deployed a Vision Transformer (ViT) pipeline for more robust feature extraction in T2-weighted MRI data.  
\hspace*{1em} Showed improved accuracy by fusing clinically relevant biomarkers and imaging data.

%-------------------------------------------
% Contrast Agent-Free HCC
%-------------------------------------------
\bigskip
\textbf{Contrast Agent-Free Approach for Enhancing HCC Visualization on CECT Derived from NCECT} \hfill \textit{Jun. 2023 -- Dec. 2023} \\
\textit{Keywords: Computer Vision, Medical Imaging, Diffusion Models, Generative Models} \quad
[\href{https://github.com/janghana/NCECT-to-CECT}{Code}] \\
\hspace*{1em} Introduced a method to enhance hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) visibility by generating pseudo-contrast-enhanced CT (CECT) from non-contrast CT (NCECT) scans. Reduced the need for multiple contrast agent injections, improving patient safety and diagnostic workflow efficiency. \\
\hspace*{1em} Employed an adversarial diffusion model to simulate vascular enhancement.  
\hspace*{1em} Achieved comparable contrast effects without repeated CA exposure.

%-------------------------------------------
% HCC Tumor Segmentation with UNETR
%-------------------------------------------
\bigskip
\textbf{Enhancing HCC Tumor Segmentation through Aortic Contrast-Enhanced Imaging with UNETR} \hfill \textit{Jun. 2023 -- Aug. 2023} \\
\textit{Keywords: Computer Vision, Medical Imaging, 3D Medical Image Segmentation} \quad
[\href{https://github.com/kimhyoree/Improving-HCC-diagnostic-precision-in-CT-using-UNETR-model}{Code}] \\
\hspace*{1em} Investigated an aorta-referenced contrast strategy to improve HCC segmentation performance. Leveraged the UNETR model to precisely identify tumor boundaries, emphasizing the contrast difference boosted by aortic imaging. \\
\hspace*{1em} Enhanced segmentation by calibrating tumor intensity with aortic contrast.  
\hspace*{1em} Demonstrated robust tumor delineation, potentially aiding early detection and treatment planning.

%-------------------------------------------
% Predictive Coding Network
%-------------------------------------------
\bigskip
\textbf{Designing a Predictive Coding Network Model to Mimic the Human Visual Cortex} \hfill \textit{Jan. 2023 -- Jun. 2023} \\
\textit{Keywords: Cognitive Neuroscience, Computer Vision, Illusory Contour, Kanizsa Triangle} \quad
[\href{https://github.com/janghana/Predictive-Coding-Network}{Code}] \\
\hspace*{1em} Explored neural mechanisms behind illusory contour processing, implementing a predictive coding network (PCN) to capture complex visual illusions akin to those in the human cortex. \\
\hspace*{1em} Demonstrated that standard CNNs struggle with illusory shapes, necessitating a predictive framework.  
\hspace*{1em} Validated PCN’s ability to handle intricacies of visual illusions beyond conventional polygon detection.

%-------------------------------------------
% Investigating "Jumping" Phenomenon
%-------------------------------------------
\bigskip
\textbf{Investigating Brainwave Patterns in Response to the “Jumping” Phenomenon} \hfill \textit{Apr. 2022 -- Oct. 2022} \\
\textit{Keywords: Cognitive Neuroscience, EEG, Illusory jumping, Machine Learning} \quad
[\href{https://github.com/janghana/EEG-data-analysis-of-128-channels}{Code} $|$ 
\href{https://drive.google.com/file/d/1BobxfhqmgHK-C1yrrsNltcuCzjpQJuR_/view}{Video}] \\
\hspace*{1em} Analyzed a “jumping” effect in rotating objects with embedded Gaussian noise, recording 128-channel EEG signals to uncover neural correlates. Explored steady-state visual potentials and alpha-range responses. \\
\hspace*{1em} Observed no SSVEP-like signals but identified peaks in the alpha band (8–13 Hz).  
- Employed machine learning classification to decode rhythmic sampling patterns linked to illusory motion.

\end{rSection}

